le polynomial of degree $r$, where $gcd(r,\nm)=1$. In particular, depending on the place $P$ and for $D$ an $Aut(F_q(x,\ny)/F_q(x))$-invariant sum of rational places of $F$ such that $P,Q_i\\notin\nsupp(D)$, we obtain necessary and sufficient conditions on $m$ and $\\beta_i$'s\nsuch that the flag has the isometry-dual property.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 09:05:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Dec 2021 17:05:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-28"}
